description:
The GVP Ontology defines classes, properties and values ([`skos:Concept`](https://triplydb.com/w3c/skos/table?subject=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2004%2F02%2Fskos%2Fcore%23Concept)s) used in GVP LOD.

As of version 3.0, it is complete regarding [AAT](/getty/aat), [TGN](/getty/tgn) and [ULAN](/getty/ulan), and will be extended in time with more elements needed for other GVP vocabularies (CONA).

It uses the [SKOS](/w3c/skos), [SKOS-XL](/w3c/skos-xl), ISO 25964; [DC](/dcmi/dce), [DCT](/dcmi/dct), [BIBO](/none/bibo), [FOAF](/none/foaf), [BIO](/none/bio), [Schema](/none/sdo), [PROV](/w3c/prov), [WGS84](/w3c/wgs84) ontologies.

Version: 3.3.0

AdminPlaceConcept.label: AdminPlaceConcept
AdminPlaceConcept.description: Place defined by administrative boundaries and conditions, including inhabited places, nations, and empires. Used in TGN only

Biography.description: Biography of a ULAN agent (schema:Person|Organization). Depending on the agent, has these fields:- schema:description: one-line-biography- gvp:estStart- schema:birthPlace | foundationLocation, pointing to TGN- gvp:estEnd- schema:deathPlace | dissolutionLocation, pointing to TGN- schema:gender, pointing to AAT (male, female, other)- dct:contributorThe fields of the preferred biogrpahy are also available in the agent.

Concept.label: Concept
Concept.description: Proper concept. Used in AAT only; TGN & ULAN have their own, e.g. gvp:PhysPlaceConcept & gvp:PersonConcept. Used for indexing and cataloguing

Facet.label: Facet
Facet.description: One of the major divisions of a vocabulary

GroupConcept.label: GroupConcept
GroupConcept.description: Two or more people who generally worked together to collectively create art. Not necessarily legally incorporated. A family of artists may be considered a "corporate body". Corresponds to crm:E74_Group, not its subclass crm:E40_Legal_Body

GuideTerm.label: GuideTerm
GuideTerm.description: Guide Term: place holder to create a level in the hierarchy. Used in AAT and ULAN. Not used for indexing or cataloguing.

Hierarchy.label: Hierarchy
Hierarchy.description: Top of a hierarchy. Used in AAT only. Not used for indexing or cataloguing

ObsoleteSubject.label: ObsoleteSubject
ObsoleteSubject.description: Obsolete subject: moved out of the publishable hierarchy, or merged to another (pointed by dct:isReplacedBy)

PersonConcept.label: PersonConcept
PersonConcept.description: A single individual. Usually people engaged in the design or creation of art or architecture ("Artists"); but may also include donors, patrons, rulers, sitters, art historians, etc ("Non-Artists")

PhysAdminPlaceConcept.label: PhysAdminPlaceConcept
PhysAdminPlaceConcept.description: Place that is both administrative and physical. Rarely used. Used in TGN only

PhysPlaceConcept.label: PhysPlaceConcept
PhysPlaceConcept.description: Physical feature, defined by its physical characteristics on planet Earth, including mountains, rivers, and oceans. Used in TGN only

ScopeNote.description: Defines a GVP subject or provides usage information. Has fields:- dc:identifier: numeric ID, also used in the URL.- rdf:value: the note itself (as per SKOS Primer: 4.2 Advanced Documentation Features) with language tag- dct:language: matches the language tag- gvp:displayOrder, order of this note amongst others- gvp:historicFlag, gvp:estStart, gvp:estEnd, rdfs:comment: Historic Information about applicability- dct:source or subproperties thereof - dct:contributor or subproperties thereof

Subject.label: Subject
Subject.description: Node in a GVP vocabulary hierarchy. May be Facet, GuideTerm, Hierarchy, Concept, AdminPlaceConcept, PhysPlaceConcept, PhysAdminPlaceConcept, or ObsoleteSubject.Implemented as skos:Concept or iso:ThesaurusArray and skos:Collection

UnknownPersonConcept.label: UnknownPersonConcept
UnknownPersonConcept.description: Unknown person representing a nationality/culture (the Unknown People by Culture facet)

aat2291_locus-setting_for.label: aat2291_locus-setting_for

broaderExtended.label: broaderExtended

broaderPartitive.label: broaderPartitive

broaderPreferredExtended.label: broaderPreferredExtended
